We are so confident in our process, expertise, and skill, I sign my name on every project we build.  We are looking to partner with like-minded developers and businesses that are looking for a signature project. Bryan Garvey, CEO of Corbet Design + Build, a boutique design build firm based in Dallas, has more than 16 years of diverse experience in the commercial construction industry. Throughout his many years in construction, Bryan has gained thorough knowledge of ground-up construction and major renovations in automotive, office, restaurant, retail, medical and public works projects, as well as historic restoration. Prior to founding Corbet Design + Build more than 10 years ago, Bryan gained vast experience in excavation construction methods and strategic planning, which resulted in an impressive history of high-quality projects. Bryan is a former member of Entrepreneurs’ Organization Dallas and is currently an active board member of the Park Cities YMCA. In his spare time, Bryan enjoys off-road racing and working on classic cars, a passion of his since childhood. During Bryan’s racing career, he has competed multiple times in the Mexican (Baja) 1000, an off-road race in Mexico’s Baja California Peninsula; Atacama Rally in Santiago, Chile; and now Dakar in South America.

Description: Native Documents has developed a pixel perfect chat-enabled viewer/editor for Microsoft Word documents, for the web, iOS and elsewhere
Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: They are the makers of a Word document editor designed for teams reliant on the web and mobile devices. Most businesses use Microsoft Office documents, and Google hasn’t altered that fact. This is because the features which were exciting and new 10 years ago, came at the cost of compatibility. They’re unique because they give you both: support for your existing documents, and a foundation for new features. Without compromise. The secret to delivering this is their proprietary layout engine, which you can think of as being WebKit for Office documents. Their customers have told us they need things like: - table of contents - headers/footers - track changes - comments - columns - complex tables So they’ve made sure these work as you’d expect, inside your browser. Much of this is still missing from Google Docs and Word Online, despite public demand. You’d think that if these features were easy to add on top of what they offer, you’d have them by now. Their customers also need to work in lengthy/complex documents, without worrying whether their browser will be able to handle it. They tell us they want all the features of Microsoft Word and not a crippled Word Online.
Founders: Florian Reuter, Gary Edwards, Jason Harrop

Worse, deals we wanted started getting lost in a flood of deals we didn't want.  That's why we put together Dealupa—a single place to find the best daily deals. We gather deals from across the web and then we use patent-pending DealRank technology to organize deals according to their quality and relevance to you.
